HEADWORD: Puzzler
<hw>Puz"zler</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who, or that
which, puzzles or perplexes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Hebrew, the general <qex>puzzler</qex> of old heads.</q>
<rj><qau>Brome.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Puzzlingly</ent>⟦br⟧
